"to\": 2863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That figure is 13 percent higher than at the same point last year.\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2964, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That figure\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2909}, {\"ngram\": \"the same point\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On June 18 this year, 882 migrants crossed the Channel in a single day.\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 3036, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 2968, \"to\": 2972}, {\"ngram\": \"882 migrants\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 2999}, {\"ngram\": \"the Channel\", \"from\": 3008, \"to\": 3019}, {\"ngram\": \"a single day\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even before he was chosen as the new prime minister, Sir Keir Starmer repeatedly promised to \\\"smash the gangs\\\" operating in France and locations further afield that facilitate human smuggling.\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3091, \"end\": 3107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sir Keir Starmer\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\"}, {\"begin\": 3162, \"end\": 3168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9906070202629528, \"rank\": 0.009316936312619905, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the new prime minister\", \"from\": 3067, \"to\": 3089}, {\"ngram\": \"the gangs\", \"from\": 3138, \"to\": 3147}, {\"ngram\": \"that facilitate human smuggling\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3229}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So far, however, he has not done anything.\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3273, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 3264, \"to\": 3272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has evoked the creation of a new \\\"Border Security Command\\\" that will give officers authority under 2008's Counter Terrorism Act to conduct stop-and-searches at the border, but it has not been created yet.\", \"from\": 3274, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the creation\", \"from\": 3288, \"to\": 3300}, {\"ngram\": \"a new \\\"Border Security Command\", \"from\": 3304, \"to\": 3334}, {\"ngram\": \"officers\", \"from\": 3351, \"to\": 3359}, {\"ngram\": \"authority\", \"from\": 3360, \"to\": 3369}, {\"ngram\": \"2008's Counter Terrorism Act\", \"from\": 3376, \"to\": 3404}, {\"ngram\": \"-searches\", \"from\": 3424, \"to\": 3433}, {\"ngram\": \"the border\", \"from\": 3437, \"to\": 3447}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Monday a spokesperson for 10 Downing Street said that \\\"summer is a challenging time\\\" for boat crossings and that \\\"we expect to see increases before we see improvements.\\\"\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3512, \"end\": 3529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/10_Downing_Street\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"10 Downing Street\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/10_Downing_Street\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/10_Downing_Street\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 3486, \"to\": 3492}, {\"ngram\": \"a spokesperson\", \"from\": 3493, \"to\": 3507}, {\"ngram\": \"summer\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3547}, {\"ngram\": \"a challenging time\", \"from\": 3551, \"to\": 3569}, {\"ngram\": \"boat crossings\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3589}, {\"ngram\": \"increases\", \"from\": 3617, \"to\": 3626}, {\"ngram\": \"improvements\", \"from\": 3641, \"to\": 3653}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The government's inaction is already a liability, as the eruption of anti-immigrant riots in the wake of the murder of three young girls last month by the British son of Rwandan immigrants showed.\", \"from\": 36